## Risk Rating: High

No confirmed compromise, but phishing is a primary initial-access vector. A single successful click on this type of link is enough to result in credential theft or malware delivery — severity is rated on potential impact, not just observed outcome.

## Recommendations

- Block sender domain and flagged URL at the email gateway/proxy level.
- Run attachment through sandbox/hash reputation check if not already done.
- Search mailbox-wide for other recipients of the same campaign (same sender/domain/subject).
- Force credential reset for the recipient if any doubt exists about link interaction.
- Reinforce phishing awareness training, particularly around urgency-based pretexts.
- Verify SPF/DKIM/DMARC enforcement is catching similar spoofing attempts.

## Detection Query Example (KQL)

```kql
EmailEvents
| where SenderFromDomain !in (KnownGoodDomains)
| where UrlCount > 0
| join EmailUrlInfo on NetworkMessageId
| where Url has_any ("suspicious-domain-pattern")
| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, RecipientEmailAddress, Subject, Url
```

